news.title: Bajaj Electricals' net profit dips 56% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Bajaj Electricals' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,142.26 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 1.82 per cent from Rs 1,163.43 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kolte Patil Developers' net loss widens to Rs 26.23 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Kolte Patil Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 204.86 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 48.70 per cent from Rs 137.77 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India posts net profit of Rs 35.80 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: HeidelbergCement India's net total income stood at Rs 580.72 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 12.31 per cent from Rs 517.06 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government likely to tweak industrial land policy
news.para: Although the state cabinet cleared the new land allotment policy at its recent meeting chaired by the chief minister YS Jagan Mohan Reddy, it had directed the industries department to ready the comprehensive plan on the issue.

news.title: Bengaluru: Apartments with STPs cry foul as BWSSB imposes sanitary fee
news.para: Sanitary charges are typically levied for wastewater removal from buildings. Apartments with more than 20 flats are required to treat their sewage by establishing sewage treatment plants (STPs) as per BWSSB rules introduced in 2014.

news.title: Pune civic body seals 40 assets over property tax dues
news.para: Property tax department head Ajit Deshmukh said, “The civic administration sent out notices to the defaulters. When they did not pay despite repeated warnings, we began the sealing process.”

news.title: Bengaluru civic body mulls seizing assets of property tax defaulters
news.para: The BBMP has set a target of collecting Rs 4,790 crore in 2023-24 under the head of property tax, including cess. Deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar had expressed his unhappiness about the collection of property tax in Bengaluru and directed the officials to pull their socks up.

news.title: Availability of land may aid Pune metro extension to Nigdi
news.para: The project, worth over Rs 900 crore, recently received the Union government’s final nod. MahaMetro said the actual work on ground is expected to begin around February.

news.title: Mumbai: More than 460 building sites get directives from civic body
news.para: ​The civic body also has threatened to issue stop-work notices or to seal the sites if the norms are not complied with at the earliest. Construction projects have been given a time-frame to comply with the norms.

news.title: Margao civic body berated for potential 45% hike in construction licence fees
news.para: The adoption of the revised rates for construction licences would have cascading effects on the common people, they cautioned.

news.title: Ranchi: 48 highrises posing threat to flights yet to reply to notices
news.para: The airport authorities have written to the urban development and housing department, seeking their cooperation in addressing the issue as the tall structures could potentially be risky to flight operations.

news.title: Lucknow: Six men dupe 20 homebuyers of Rs 10 lakh each
news.para: Those booked, under sections 420 (cheating) and 406 (breach of trust), included Devkush of Aliganj, Vivekanand and Manish Srivastava of Gudamba, Jai Prakash, Ved Prakash and Virendra Kumar Sharma.

news.title: DRI conducts search operation at Havells India corporate office
news.para: "The Directorate of Revenue Intelligence has conducted a search at the Corporate office of the Company viz. Havells India Limited in Noida, which concluded this morning on 4th November 2023 at around 2:20 am," Havells India said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: HC admits PIL alleging CRZ violation by Panvel civic body for slum rehabilitation
news.para: The PIL also mentions that the low lying plot is located alongside the confluence of Gadhi river and Panvel creek and floods every year.

news.title: YEIDA to sell plots for hotel projects in Greater Noida
news.para: However, structures exceeding 24m in height will require clearance from the Airports Authority of India (AAI). Furthermore, the master plan for development of hotels will be determined keeping in mind all conditions of YEIDA.

news.title: DDA seeks consultant firm for carrying out demolition of Signature Views Apartments, issues RFP
news.para: Constructed in 2007-2009, the complex comprises 336 flats, including both HIG and MIG. Shortly after, however, the flats started facing construction-related issues, forcing the residents to complain to the DDA.

news.title: Maharashtra government banks on GIS mapping for realistic RR rates in 2024
news.para: RR rates are the rates of residential property land or commercial properties for a given area published by the state government after assessment. The rates are announced at the beginning of a financial year.

news.title: Keystone Realtors posts net profit of Rs 4.17 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Keystone Realtors' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 633.33 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 1,036.63 per cent from Rs 55.72 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
